%% TrustyAI Explainability - Data Flow Diagram
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6
%% Source: architecture/rhoai-3.0/trustyai-explainability.md

sequenceDiagram
    participant MM as ModelMesh Serving
    participant KS as KServe Inference Logger
    participant CE as ConsumerEndpoint<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant CC as CloudEventConsumer<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant R as InferencePayload<br/>Reconciler
    participant S as Storage Backend<br/>(PVC/MinIO/DB)
    participant PS as PrometheusScheduler<br/>(periodic timer)
    participant PP as PrometheusPublisher<br/>(Micrometer gauges)
    participant P as Prometheus<br/>80/TCP HTTP
    participant Client as Client<br/>(via auth proxy)
    participant EX as Explainer<br/>(LIME/SHAP/CF)
    participant ME as Model Endpoint<br/>(KServe/ModelMesh)

    Note over MM,S: Flow 1: ModelMesh Payload Ingestion
    MM->>CE: POST /consumer/kserve/v2<br/>HTTP 80/TCP, No Auth
    CE->>R: Partial inference payload
    R->>R: Reconcile input/output pairs
    R->>S: Store complete prediction record

    Note over KS,S: Flow 2: KServe CloudEvent Ingestion
    KS->>CC: CloudEvent (org.kubeflow.serving.<br/>inference.request/response)<br/>HTTP 8080/TCP
    CC->>R: Parsed inference payload
    R->>R: Reconcile input/output pairs
    R->>S: Store complete prediction record

    Note over PS,P: Flow 3: Scheduled Metric Computation
    PS->>S: Read stored inference data
    S-->>PS: Prediction records
    PS->>PS: Compute SPD, DIR, KS Test,<br/>MMD, Meanshift metrics
    PS->>PP: Update Micrometer gauges<br/>(trustyai_spd, trustyai_dir, etc.)
    P->>PP: GET /q/metrics<br/>HTTP 80/TCP, Bearer Token
    PP-->>P: Prometheus gauge values

    Note over Client,ME: Flow 4: Explainer Computation (disabled in RHOAI)
    Client->>EX: POST /explainers/local/lime<br/>HTTP 80/TCP, via auth proxy
    EX->>ME: Invoke model inference<br/>gRPC/HTTP (variable port)
    ME-->>EX: Prediction result
    EX->>EX: Compute explanation<br/>(LIME/SHAP/Counterfactual)
    EX-->>Client: Explanation response<br/>HTTP 80/TCP
